Finish equipment system (equip, unequip, view, etc..)


on world create, ask if game is creative or normal
creative mode gets cheats (nodeath, get item, goto location, givexp)





task speed is the time it takes to do any action (default: 100)
when the player is completing a task that takes time:
    time = time/(task_speed/100)






### SKILLS ###

each character has a multitude of stats
each stat effects the player positively, when they level up in that specific stat
example: combat gives more crit damage
         defence gives more defence
         constitution gives more max health
         woodcutting gives more strength
         carpentry gives more inteligence and task speed

some game mechanics require a stat to be above a specific level

stat xp can be gained from different activities
example: gain combat xp from killing creatures
         gain defence xp from taking damage
         gain constitution xp from staying in battle for longer
         gain woodcutting xp from cutting trees
         gain carpentry xp from crafting items

##############






### COMBAT REWORK ###

each creature and character has an initiative stat
whoever has the highest initiative, starts first
the list is created from highest initiative to lowest

go through everyone in the list, and they will use their action
repeat through the list

if someone dies, remove them from the list

when the list doesnt have any characters or creatures, the fight ends

#####################






### EFFECTS ###

an effect can be given to a character or creature
the effect will have a specific time until it stops
each turn, the value lowers

each effect has a power value, that increases the effects

there are different types of effects:
    turn based: an event happens every turn
    event based: an event is modified by the effect
    unlock: the effect unlocks a specific game mechanic

effects:
    strength: multiplies damage dealt by 1.2x (event based)
    weakness: multiplies damage dealt by 0.8x (event based)
    poison: multiplies damage taken by 1.2x (event based)

###############






### LEVEL ###

each character has a level
the player gets xp from nearly every activity
leveling up is more dificult than leveling up skills

each level, the player gets better stats, unlocks, etc..
    +10 Aggro

the player also gets a skill point, and can be applied on any skill to increase xp gain by 1.2x (stackable)

#############






### CRAFTING ###

the party has a vector of unlocked crafting recipes
new recipes can be gained from blueprints, quests, buying, leveling up, searching locations, enemies, etc..

the crafting menu displays the first 20 recipes, and has a page system to scroll
you can alternatively search for the recipes

when crafting, it will check if the player meets the requirements, is at the correct bench, has the items, has inventory space, etc..

after crafting, you will gain xp

some recipes have a wait time

you can craft multiple items at same time (if there is a wait time, combine the time)

some recipes have item requirements, that arent removed after a craft

#################






### QUESTS ###

when talking to an npc, check if a quest is being operated by the npc.
if the player is completing a quest by the npc, display a menu showing the start_msg and specific task.
add an option to talk to the npc normally, or leave

activate quests by talking to an npc, by going through specific dialogue
end quests by talking to the specfic npc

when an objective is complete, move on to the next one
objective types can be a node (when an event is created, it will send a node with info)
                       an item (return items to npc)

node types:
  get.item: checks if player picked up items
  kill.creature: checks when player kills a creature
  damage.creature: checks when player damages a creature, add damage to value
  explore.specific.location: checks when the player enters a location
  explore.new.location: checks when the player enters a location, and adds it to array if it doesnt exist. stores all areas, and can be used to check if player explored significant area
  buy.item
  sell.item
  craft.item
  talk.npc
  getxp.level
  getxp.skill.skillname

